.TH "user_exp_rcv_clear" 9 "user_exp_rcv_clear" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
user_exp_rcv_clear \- Clear the given tid rcv list
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" user_exp_rcv_clear
.BI "(struct hfi1_filedata *fd "  ","
.BI "unsigned long arg "  ","
.BI "u32 len "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "fd" 12
file data of the current driver instance
.IP "arg" 12
ioctl argumnent for user space information
.IP "len" 12
length of data structure associated with ioctl command
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
The \fBhfi1_user_exp_rcv_clear\fP can be called from the error path.  Because
of this, we need to use this wrapper to copy the user space information
before doing the clear.
